There's some incorrect text in the commenting of Graphics/Texture2D.h, return height should be depth here:
```
/// Return height.
int GetDepth() const { return depth_; }
```
(I don't have an up-to-date copy of the repository, or I'd just make a pull request)

Here is simple example:
```
    std::cout << "Node is type of Node = " << std::boolalpha << Urho3D::Node::IsTypeOf("Node") << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Node is type of Scene = " << std::boolalpha << Urho3D::Node::IsTypeOf("Scene") << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Scene is type of Node = " << std::boolalpha << Urho3D::Scene::IsTypeOf("Node") << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Scene is type of Scene = " << std::boolalpha << Urho3D::Scene::IsTypeOf("Scene") << std::endl;
    
    std::cout << "Node is type of Node = " << std::boolalpha << Urho3D::Node::IsTypeOf<Urho3D::Node>() << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Node is type of Scene = " << std::boolalpha << Urho3D::Node::IsTypeOf<Urho3D::Scene>() << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Scene is type of Node = " << std::boolalpha << Urho3D::Scene::IsTypeOf<Urho3D::Node>() << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Scene is type of Scene = " << std::boolalpha << Urho3D::Scene::IsTypeOf<Urho3D::Scene>() << std::endl;
```

My output is:
```
Node is type of Node = false
Node is type of Scene = false
Scene is type of Node = false
Scene is type of Scene = false
Node is type of Node = false
Node is type of Scene = false
Scene is type of Node = false
Scene is type of Scene = false
```

It must be fail because in static implementation of Object::IsTypeOf uses static Object::GetTypeInfoStatic instead of T::GetTypeInfoStatic. Adding IsTypeOf into URHO3D_OBJECT can fix it.

